   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Transformative Education for Refugees in Zimbabwe</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The USAP Community School is a residential 11th and 12th grade (A Level) school in Zimbabwe that educates high-achieving, low-income students to excel at the world&apos;s top universities with the aim of building society.  In 2021, we have a total of 7 students (10% of our students) from Tongogara Refugee Camp.  This project will raise funds for us to be able to continue covering all costs for refugee students to access the high quality and transformative value-based education our school provides.</narrative>
  </description>
